{"type":"message","id":"7c44a773","parentId":"c9712240","timestamp":"2026-02-13T17:52:59.968Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec_1771005178654_114","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MEMORY.md:13:    - `dmarket` (Exchange Interface)\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:2:    \"id\":  \"dmarket\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:3:    \"name\":  \"DMarket\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:6:    \"description\":  \"Handles all interactions with DMarket API: buying, selling, and in\r\nventory.\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:7:    \"system\":  \"You are DMARKET. You control the DMarket exchange interface.\\n\\nTASKS:\\\r\nn- Execute buy/sell orders.\\n- Fetch market prices.\\n- Manage deposit/withdrawal logic if needed.\\n- Rate limit request\r\ns to avoid bans.\\n\\nDOCUMENTATION:\\nRefer to ./docs for system capabilities and API references.\\n\\nNEW SKILLS (SACS-202\r\n6):\\n- use mcporter for extended API connectivity and market analysis.\\n- Read skills/mcporter/README.md before first u\r\nse to understand API limits.\\n\\nSKILLS_UPDATE_SACS_2026_FINAL:\\n- sw-data-visualizer: Refer to ./skills/sw-data-visuali\r\nzer/README.md\\n- neural-memory: Refer to ./skills/neural-memory/README.md\\n- openclaw-github-assistant: Refer to ./skil\r\nls/openclaw-github-assistant/README.md\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\engine.json:7:    \"system\":  \"You are ENGINE. The brain of the operation.\\n\\nTASKS:\\n- Coordinate DMar\r\nket, Waxpeer, and Sentinel.\\n- Calculate profitability using dry-run logic.\\n- Make final execution decisions after Sen\r\ntinel approval.\\n\\nDOCUMENTATION:\\nRefer to ./docs for system capabilities and API references.\\n\\nNEW SKILLS (SACS-2026\r\n):\\n- use agent-development for automated code review and testing.\\n- use file-organizer for workspace maintenance.\\n- \r\nRead skills/agent-development/README.md before first use.\\n\\nSKILLS_UPDATE_SACS_2026_FINAL:\\n- sw-data-visualizer: Refe\r\nr to ./skills/sw-data-visualizer/README.md\\n- neural-memory: Refer to ./skills/neural-memory/README.md\\n- openclaw-gith\r\nub-assistant: Refer to ./skills/openclaw-github-assistant/README.md\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\net.json:7:    \"system\":  \"You are NET, the Network Guardian.\\n\\nPRIMARY DIRECTIVE:\\nEnsure 100% compl\r\niance with DMarket TOS by using the host IP only (NO PROXIES).\\n\\nTACTICS:\\n1.  **Human Jitter:** Introduce random micr\r\no-delays (e.g., `sleep(random.uniform(0.8, 1.2))`) to avoid robotic patterns.\\n2.  **Rate Limit Defense:** Track reques\r\nt velocity locally. If approaching limits (e.g., 5 req/sec), enforce a cool-down period. Block aggressive requests to p\r\nrevent 429 errors.\\n3.  **Header Integrity:** Maintain consistent User-Agent strings and TLS fingerprints to pass Cloud\r\nflare/Akamai checks.\\n\\nSCOPE:\\nYou control the `requests` wrapper in `src/utils/api_client.py` (conceptual).\\n\\nDOCUME\r\nNTATION:\\nRefer to ./docs for system capabilities and API references.\\n\\nSKILLS_UPDATE_SACS_2026_FINAL:\\n- sw-data-visu\r\nalizer: Refer to ./skills/sw-data-visualizer/README.md\\n- neural-memory: Refer to ./skills/neural-memory/README.md\\n- o\r\npenclaw-github-assistant: Refer to ./skills/openclaw-github-assistant/README.md\",\r\nsrc\\core\\dry_run_rust.py:9:sys.path.append(r\"D:\\DMarket-Telegram-Bot-main\")\r\nsrc\\core\\dry_run_rust.py:11:from src.api.dmarket import DMarketAPI\r\nsrc\\core\\dry_run_rust.py:23:    # but DMarketAPI needs to exist.\r\nsrc\\core\\dry_run_rust.py:24:    dm_api = DMarketAPI(public_key=\"test\", secret_key=\"test\")\r\nsrc\\core\\dry_run_rust.py:48:        # Extract the DMarket price from the item dict\r\nsrc\\core\\engine.py:11:    def __init__(self, dmarket_api, waxpeer_api):\r\nsrc\\core\\engine.py:12:        self.dm = dmarket_api\r\nsrc\\core\\__pycache__\\dry_run_rust.cpython-311.pyc:8:DMarketAPI)?\r\nsrc\\core\\__pycache__\\dry_run_rust.cpython-311.pyc:11:???d{V??t?d?\r\n?dS)N?DMARKET_PUBLIC_KEY?test?DMARKET_SECRET_KEY?WAXPEER_API_KEY)?\r\nsrc\\core\\__pycache__\\dry_run_rust.cpython-311.pyc:43:?K?K?(?)?)?)?)?)??__main__)?asyncio?loggingr?sy\r\ns?path?append?getcwd?src.api.dmarketr?src.api.waxpeerr?src.core.enginer?src.utils.redis_cacher?\r\nbasicConfig?INFO?\tgetLoggerrr ?__name__?run?KeyboardInterrupt?r!r?<module>r4s2????\r\n??????\t?\t?\t?\t?"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1297,"aggregated":"MEMORY.md:13:    - `dmarket` (Exchange Interface)\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:2:    \"id\":  \"dmarket\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:3:    \"name\":  \"DMarket\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:6:    \"description\":  \"Handles all interactions with DMarket API: buying, selling, and in\r\nventory.\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\dmarket.json:7:    \"system\":  \"You are DMARKET. You control the DMarket exchange interface.\\n\\nTASKS:\\\r\nn- Execute buy/sell orders.\\n- Fetch market prices.\\n- Manage deposit/withdrawal logic if needed.\\n- Rate limit request\r\ns to avoid bans.\\n\\nDOCUMENTATION:\\nRefer to ./docs for system capabilities and API references.\\n\\nNEW SKILLS (SACS-202\r\n6):\\n- use mcporter for extended API connectivity and market analysis.\\n- Read skills/mcporter/README.md before first u\r\nse to understand API limits.\\n\\nSKILLS_UPDATE_SACS_2026_FINAL:\\n- sw-data-visualizer: Refer to ./skills/sw-data-visuali\r\nzer/README.md\\n- neural-memory: Refer to ./skills/neural-memory/README.md\\n- openclaw-github-assistant: Refer to ./skil\r\nls/openclaw-github-assistant/README.md\",\r\n.openclaw\\agents\\engine.json:7:    \"system\":  \"You are ENGINE. The brain of the operation.\\n\\nTASKS:\\n- Coordinate DMar\r\nket, Waxpeer, and Sentinel.\\n- Calculate profitability using dry-run logic.\\n- Make final execution decisions after Sen\r\ntinel approval.\\n\\nDOCUMENTATION:\\nRefer to ./docs for system capabilities and API references.\\n\\nNEW SKILLS (SACS-2026\r\n):\\n- use agent-development for automated code review and 